<item>
            <title>[CXF-8645] Fix default authentication scheme for JWT authentication filter</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-8645</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The default authentication scheme is as per spec &quot;Bearer&quot;. This is described in &lt;a href=&quot;https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc6750&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;RFC 6750&lt;/a&gt; &#160;and the &lt;a href=&quot;https://swagger.io/docs/specification/authentication/bearer-authentication/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;OAS spec&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For backwards compatibility you can fix this by setting the property &quot;expectedAuthScheme&quot; of JwtAuthenticationFilter to &quot;Bearer&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the next major version the default should be updated and mentioned in the migration guide.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
